            <div type="translation" resp="part:vagi part:emfr">
                
                <p n="1">
                    Prosperity! Fortune! 
                </p>
                <p n="1">
                    14th year of Kōpparakesarivarman.
                </p>
                <p n="1-9">
                    I, Kāśyapa Candraśekhara Bhaṭṭa, <supplied reason="subaudible">one among</supplied> the three thousand seven hundred <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>mu-v-āyiratt-ēḻu-ṉūṟṟu</foreign></supplied>, lord of the shrine <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>śrī-kōyil-uṭaiyān</foreign><note>That is in fact a servant of the temple.</note></supplied> of big Śrī Vāṉavan-mahādevi-caturvedimaṅgalam, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> of the northern bank,
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">agrees</supplied>
                    with<note>Literally: to.</note> Veṇṇampi, the officer <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>karmmi</foreign>, that is, <foreign>kaṉmi</foreign></supplied> of Vikramacōḻa Mahārāja alias Ampalavam Paḻuvūr Nakkaṉ, lord <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>uṭaiyāṉ</foreign></supplied> of Kuvaḷālaiyam, who caused to raise <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eḻuntaruḷḷuvitta</foreign></supplied> in stone <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kallāl</foreign></supplied> the holy sanctuary <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>śrī-vimāna</foreign></supplied> of the shrine <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kōyil</foreign></supplied> of the god <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>devar</foreign></supplied> of this Śrī Vijayamaṅgalam,
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">that</supplied>
                    Viravalli Tirunilakaṇṭa Kramavitta, <supplied reason="subaudible">one among</supplied> the great people <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaṇperumakkal</foreign></supplied> of this glorious temple, 
                    
                    he <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ivan</foreign></supplied> as supervisor<!--EF supervision by the sabhaiyār--> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaṇkāṇiyāka</foreign></supplied> of those of the Sabhā <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>sabhaiyār</foreign></supplied>, 
                    
                    after excluding <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nīkki</foreign></supplied> the gold <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>poṉ</foreign></supplied>,
                    
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">would be provided</supplied>,
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">with</supplied>
                    the <foreign>piṭilikaivāri</foreign>, 
                    
                    four holy <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s for midday <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ucampōtu</foreign></supplied> including on Grahaṇa Saṅkrānti Viṣu 
                    and
                    four <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s at midnight <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>atthayāma</foreign>, that is, <foreign>arddhayāma</foreign></supplied>
                    
                    for these eight Brahmins <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iy</foreign><supplied reason="subaudible"><foreign>u</foreign></supplied><foreign>paripārkaḷu eṭṭukku</foreign></supplied><!--EF: not clear that Brahmins are mentioned here-->.
                </p>
                <p n="10-11">
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">Accordingly</supplied>, I have to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ekaṭavēn</foreign>, that is, <foreign>erikaṭavēn</foreign></supplied> one evening lamp for one time in the evening twilight <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>antiyam</foreign></supplied>.
                </p>
                <p n="11-12">
                    I have to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eṟa</foreign>, that is, <foreign>eri</foreign>?</supplied> five lamps for three times at the juctures of the days; I have to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eṟṟa</foreign>, that is, <foreign>era</foreign>?</supplied> two lamps <supplied reason="subaudible">for</supplied> one time of holy offering <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>śrī palli</foreign>, that is, <foreign>pali</foreign></supplied>.
                </p>
                <p n="12-13">
                    I have to offer <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>paṭaikka</foreign></supplied> one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> of ghee food offering <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ney amutil</foreign></supplied> for holy food offerings; having placed <supplied reason="subaudible">for</supplied> two times with this temple officer <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ippiṭillikaivāri</foreign></supplied> two <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nāṟuṭi</foreign>, that is, <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>?</supplied> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> and oil at the rate of one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> for food offering <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>amutukku</foreign></supplied> and lamp oil <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>viḷakkeṇṇai</foreign></supplied> for one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> and two <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s everyday.
                </p>
                <p n="13-14">
                    I have to place for vegetable food offering <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaṟiyamutu</foreign></supplied> with two <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s of paddy everyday.
                </p>
                <p n="14-16">
                    So that there be <supplied reason="subaudible"><foreign>āka</foreign></supplied> five arecanuts <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>pākku</foreign></supplied> at the time of the two junctures, <supplied reason="subaudible">thus</supplied> ten arecanuts <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>aṭaikkāy</foreign></supplied>,  
                    
                    I, myself, have to do so <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ippaṭi ceyya kaṭavēṉ nāṉē</foreign></supplied>
                    
                    with the supervisors <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaṇkāṇiyōṭu</foreign></supplied> of that day <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>aṉṟāṭṭu</foreign></supplied> 
                    
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">for</supplied> that much <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ittaṉaiyum</foreign></supplied>
                    designated <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iccuṭṭapaṭa</foreign>, that is, <foreign>iccuṭṭapaṭṭa</foreign></supplied> 
                    
                    betel <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>veṟṟilai</foreign></supplied> food offering needed <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vēṇṭu</foreign></supplied>
                    
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">for</supplied> those <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ivai</foreign></supplied> thirty <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>mūpattu</foreign></supplied> dry ginger <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cukku</foreign></supplied>.                                        
                    
                    
                </p></div>
            
